Soft Ginger Cookies  - low FODMAP - gf
  --Jessica Kellgren-Fozard

190 g (1 c) dairy free spread (or 13 1/2 tbsp butter)
200 g (1 c) sucralose sweetener
2 large eggs
4 tbsp sugar-free syrup
150 g (1.56 c) almond flour
200 g (1.79 c) coconut flour
1 tsp baking soda
3/4 tsp ground cinnamon
1/2 tsp ground cloves
1/4 tsp salt
1 tsp guar gum (or xantham gum)

Preheat oven to 180C/350F. Soften the dairy free spread slightly but don't melt; place in a large bowl with the sweetener and mix until light and fluffy. Then mix in eggs and syrup. In a separate large bowl, whisk together the flours, spices, and guar gum until well combined. Mix the wet and dry ingredients toghether until well combined. Line a cookie sheet with parchment paper or silicon mat. Scoop the batter onto the tray and flatten each cookie so that they are even. Bake for 10-12 min until the edges turn golden and the top starts to crack. Remove from oven and let cool for 2 min before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely.


Notes: cup measurement is untested
